cs.CR, cs.IR, cs.NI, cs.SE, cs.DC 

The paper discusses security and privacy issues in the context of Cloud computing and IoT, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. 

- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on security and privacy issues. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper discusses the analysis of different components of Cloud computing and IoT. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper discusses the synergy between Cloud and IoT. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses current security and privacy preservation solutions and proposes future directions. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the paper discusses the components of Cloud computing and IoT, which are often implemented using distributed systems.
